  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 7.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Why did Moses then command?",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " If, as you assert, God ordained that marriage should be indissoluble, how comes it that Moses commanded (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐνετείλατο",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") us to practise divorce, and prescribed rules as to its conduct? They are referring to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 24:1, 2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
